</taxonomicName>
Horn, 1882 by original designation. Etymology (original). From the Latin 
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="832" pageNumber="833">infernus</emphasis>
(hell) and the Greek 
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="832" pageNumber="833">philos</emphasis>
